    "long_instructions": "### Add Variation using the Play Sequential block\r\n\r\nUsing the `play sequential` block will cue up a series of sounds to play one after the other. When a play sequential block is in a play together block, you can seamlessly layer each sound over the backtrack. \r\n\r\n**Do this:** \r\n- Add sounds to each loop to create a backtrack that lasts at least 12 measures.\r\n- Add sounds to the `play sequential` and adjust the amount of sounds or the loop so they start and end and the same time. \r\n",
